_________________________________________________________________ 

Finally, details on all of Curtis' films available for download (whether or not in this torrent, chronologically): 

1984 Inquiry: The Great British Housing Disaster 

On Britain's system-built housing of the 1960's. There's nothing wrong with the film, but I can't recommend it unless you want to watch everything you can of what he's done. There's little hint of the signature depth, brilliance, and composition of his later work. He did not narrate it. 



1992 Pandora's Box: A Fable from the Age of Science 

With this film, Curtis' familiar 'voice' and narration arrives. As do some threads and substance which appear much later in his best work. It lacks the strong unifying themes of his later work, but it contains much that is very interesting and not repeated later, so Curtis fans such as me will enjoy it. 

The broad theme is the tragicomic consequences of political and technocratic rationalism. Over six hours it examines: 

1. the establishment of economic systems in the Soviet Union, 
2. the systems and game theory of the Cold War, 
3. the 1970s UK economy, 
4. DDT, 
5. Ghana in the 1950s and 1960s, and 
6. nuclear power. 
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0437029/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0437029/&lt;/a&gt; 8.2 IMDb rating  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pandora's_Box_(television_documentary_series)&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pandora's_Box_(television_documentary_series)&lt;/a&gt;

1995 The Living Dead: Three Films about the Power of the Past 

Each part examines an example of the impacts of manipulation of history and/or memory, both national and individual. Over three hours it navigates: 

1. False narratives imposed upon WW2, 
2. Brainwashing and mind control, and 
3. UK Prime Minister Thatcher's invocation of an imperial past to enhance her power. 
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0437020/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0437020/&lt;/a&gt; 7.7  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Living_Dead_(television_documentary_series)&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Living_Dead_(television_documentary_series)&lt;/a&gt; 

1996 25 Million Pounds 

Very interesting story of a derivatives trader whose $1.3 billion loss through massive fraud caused the 1995 collapse of one of Britain's oldest and most prestigious banks. 
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/25_Million_Pounds&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/25_Million_Pounds&lt;/a&gt; 

1997 Modern Times: The Way of All Flesh (a new, first available complete version) 

The interesting story, subsequently told in a 2010 book, of the uncommon, immortal cancer cells of Henrietta Lacks. 
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0796719/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0796719/&lt;/a&gt; 8.0  &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.archive.org/details/AdamCurtisTheWayofAllFlesh&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.archive.org/details/AdamCurtisTheWayofAllFlesh&lt;/a&gt; 

None of the versions of this film which I downloaded were complete (or in high quality). So I joined a pair of partial versions to make this new, and only available complete, version of this film, at 58 minutes 45.64 seconds. 

(Some versions were missing the first 2 minutes 20 seconds. The other versions had the initial 2 minutes 20 seconds, but for some reason a total of 4Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â¾ minutes had been edited out of them in multiple spots. Before joining the files at the 2 minutes 20 seconds point with AviDemux 2.5.5, I used it on the first 2 minutes 20 seconds to match the resolution, audio bitrate, and codec of the remainder. Then I used VirtualDubMod 1.5.10.2 and mp3DirectCut 2.13 to remove a little audio noise created at the join point.) 

1999 The Mayfair Set 

Engaging film on damage to the UK economy by predatory capitalists during the Thatcher years. 
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0283201/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
