http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Mayfair_Set&lt;/a&gt; 

2002 The Century of the Self 

Curtis' most important and most fundamental film. About how corporations and governments throughout the 20th century used Freud's theories to profoundly manipulate the masses by controlling their unconscious minds. This film has my very highest recommendation.
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0432232/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0432232/&lt;/a&gt; 8.9 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Century_of_the_Self&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Century_of_the_Self&lt;/a&gt; 

2004 The Power of Nightmares 

The second of Curtis' three most important films. On the use of fear to gain political power. Compares the rises of the US Neo-Conservative, and the radical Islamist, movements. Argues that the threat of radical Islamism as a massive, sinister organized force of destruction, specifically in the form of al-Qaeda, was a myth perpetrated by the Neo-cons. 
