2011 All Watched Over By Machines of Loving Grace

Very interesting, though I think Curtis' most flawed film. Ventures a parallel between Ayn Rand's ideology and the Internet, despite how undemocratic the former is. Tends to oversimplify, for example in contrasting self-regulation with change; in practice systems both evolve and self-regulate. Claims that computers have failed to liberate us and instead have &quot;distorted and simplified our view of the world around us&quot;. 
